{"lemma":"مِحْوَرِ","slug":"مِحْوَرِ","root":"ح.#.ر","root_slug":"ح-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9469","n9473","n9474"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"axis, pivot"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"core, heart, center"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dough roller"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun from حَارَ (ḥāra, “to turn”, intransitive)."},"ipa":["/miħ.war/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9469","headword_ar":"مِحْوَرٌ","root":"Hwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pin of wood, or,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is sometimes the case,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron, on which the sheave of a pulley turns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that unites the bent piece of iron which is on each side of the sheave of a pulley, and in which it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHwr","text_ar":"محور"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is inserted, and the sheave itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood which unites"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajomaEu","text_ar":"تَجْمَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sheave of a large pulley"},{"kind":"page_break","n":667},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with what is on each side of the latter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it seems to mean here, also, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pivot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) some say that it is so called because it turns round, returning to the point from which it departed: others, that it is so called because, by its revolving, it is polished so that it becomes white: (Zj:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAwiru","text_ar":"مَحَاوِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliqato maHaAwiruhu","text_ar":"قَلِقَتْ مَحَاوِرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became unsettled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) from the state of the pin of the sheave of a pulley when it becomes smooth, and the hole becomes large, so that it wabbles. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which turns the tongue of a buckle at the end of a waist-belt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An iron instrument for cauterizing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a circular form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 2]. (K.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wooden implement"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the baker,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"maker of bread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which he expands the dough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and prepares it, and makes it round, to put it into the hot ashes in which it is baked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) so called because of its turning round upon the dough, as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHwr","text_ar":"محور"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sheave of a pulley, and because of its roundness. (T.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Zj","A","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n9473","headword_ar":"مُحَوَّرٌ","root":"Hwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Dough"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the surface has been moistened with water, so that it is shining."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 2.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyunN muHaw~araAtN","text_ar":"اَعْيُنٌ مُحَوَّرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a verse of El- 'Ajjáj,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eyes of a clear white"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the white parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and intensely black in the black parts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A2-  A boot"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lined with skin of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawarN","text_ar":"حَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9474","headword_ar":"مُحَوِّرٌ","root":"Hwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A possessor of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bread, such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw~aAraY","text_ar":"حُوَّارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}